Can you install the latest version and try again?

@pluskid what's your settings and results on k80s?

#1074 is trying to improve the performance

and you can just use allreduce_test to test your hardware bandwidth on allreduce https://github.com/NVIDIA/nccl

@piiswrong it takes effect only if compiled with `USE_NCCL=1`. i think the bug is due to nccl and a future version of nccl will fix it

@tqchen i don't think have another allreduce interface is good idea, i didn't see potential speedup on performance, but we need to maintain and test two different interfaces. while adding `push_pull` on kvstore which is almost equal to `allreduce` allow us to take advantage of other allreduce implementations. 

since it goes nowhere, i will close the PR and throw away the codes
